FORMER ANC MP Vytjie Mentor wants to stop President Jacob Zuma&rsquo;s bid to halt the release of the public protector&rsquo;s &ldquo;State capture&rdquo; report.She alleged in March that the Gupta family, which has close ties to Zuma, offered her the job of minister of public enterprises in 2010 in exchange for cancelling SAA routes to India.Mentor yesterday filed papers with the High Court in Pretoria seeking to intervene in the president&rsquo;s application to halt the publication of the report. The matter will be heard on Tuesday. Mentor has laid out details of the meeting she attended at the Guptas&rsquo; Saxonwold home in Joburg.&ldquo;I declined the ministerial job and told the Gupta representatives that they lacked the authority to make such an offer. &ldquo;As I was leaving, the president entered the room,&rdquo; she wrote in her affidavit. &ndash; NEWS24